notes: 12th Men: Yasir Hameed (Pakistan) and XM Marshall (West Indies)
RR Sarwan retired hurt at 23/1 (6.3 ov) (struck on the right elbow by a delivery from Naved-ul-Hasan)
West Indies 339/4: Highest ODI total at Adelaide Oval (prev. Australia 329/5 v India, Carlton & United Series, 1999/00)

milestones.description: Brian Lara has scored 75 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for WI breaking Haynes's record
This is the highest match aggregate (620) involving teams West Indies & Pakistan in ODIs

stories.title: Lara's cracking 156 seals emphatic win
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v West Indies, VB Series, Adelaide
stories.summary: Brian Lara marked his 250th one-day international with a magical century that included a whirlwind 106 runs from his last 57 balls and kept West Indies' finals hopes alive
